│ (L->contains(I->getParent()) &&                              │
│ !isa<Constant>(I))\n```\nThis change ensures that only       │
│ non-constant instructions defined within the loop are added  │
│ to the `ExitValues` map, preventing the crash.\n\n5.         │
│ **Conclusion**: This small change correctly handles cases    │
│ where loop-exit values are constants, making the `peelLoop`  │
│ utility more robust, especially after other optimizations    │
│ like constant folding have run."})                           │
